The United States and Italy have a strong partnership in global security, working together on various international security and humanitarian efforts such as the Counter-ISIL Coalition, Afghanistan, Syria, Libya, and the refugee crisis in the Mediterranean. Italy is a leading partner in counterterrorism efforts and contributes significantly to the Counter-ISIL Coalition. They are also involved in training police forces in Iraq and providing troops for the Resolute Support Mission in Afghanistan. Italy is the second-largest host to U.S. troops in Europe, and the two countries have a close economic relationship with significant trade and investment ties. They also collaborate in the areas of science, technology, and innovation, particularly in addressing climate change and promoting clean energy development. Cultural exchange programs and educational ties between the two countries are also robust.